I am afraid not, but a good question!
 
There is a different energy around us at different times. However, most of us are not capable of identifying it. A yogi with zero ego and very pure consciousness may be able to identify, but not others who see the world through the colors of their dense I-ness. How can one identify the color of an object seen through a dark window accurately, when the window darkens everything?
 
I was mentioning to a yogi some Rudrabhaishekas that were happening here last month, on the occasion of Kaarthika month (supposed to be dear to Shiva). He actually told me, "Narasimha, this somehow does not *feel* to me like Kaarthika month. There is some error somewhere."
 
