> People name the lunar months these days based on the raasi occupied by Moon at the time of Sun-Moon conjunction, i.e. end of Amaavaasya. Sun-Moon conjunction in Pisces begins Chaitra month, in Aries begins Vaisakha month and so on. However, is this perfect or has an error been introduced in the last few millennia due to deepening Kali?
